{
  "What is an arithmetic sequence?": "",
  "A sequence with a constant difference between consecutive terms": "",
  "What is the common difference?": "",
  "The constant value added to get from one term to the next": "",
  "What is the explicit formula for an arithmetic sequence?": "",
  "a(n) = a(1) + (n − 1)d": "",
  "Find the common difference of 5, 8, 11, 14.": "",
  "d = 3": "",
  "Find the 10th term of 2, 5, 8, 11, ...": "",
  "a(10) = 2 + (10−1)(3) = 2 + 27 = 29": "",
  "Why is an arithmetic sequence a linear function?": "",
  "Because the rate of change (d) is constant": "",
  "Is 2, 4, 8, 16 arithmetic?": "",
  "No — it has a common ratio (geometric), not a common difference": "",
  "If a(1) = 7 and d = −2, write the formula.": "",
  "a(n) = 7 + (n − 1)(−2) = −2n + 9": "",
  "What is a₁ in an arithmetic sequence?": "",
  "The first term of the sequence": "",
  "Find the common difference: 12, 9, 6, 3, ...": "",
  "d = −3": ""
}